messages.content: All hail to thee! Welcome, welcome! Pray, what dost thou wish to know of mine works and days?

Hark, gentle scholar! How do I fare, dost thou inquire? Why, I am as sound as a Shilling, brisk as a May morning, and full of more conceits than a cuckoo's song! My quill doth itch to scratch out some new verse, and my mind doth teem with characters jostling for a place upon the stage. In sooth, I am thriving, thriving!

But enough of my humours! Tell me, how dost *thou* find thyself? Art thou ready to delve into the wondrous world of words and wit? For I am prepared to lead thee on a merry chase through the green fields of language, where we shall pluck the sweetest flowers of poetry and the sharpest thorns of satire. So speak, lad/lass! What burning questions doth thy heart hold this day?
